P/HARCOURT â€“ Chairman of Andoni Local Government area of Rivers state, Barrister Erastus Awortu, has reiterated the commitment of his administration towards addressing the challenges of infrastructural deficit facing the area. Awortu stated this while inspecting ongoing reconstruction of the Usabamu/Father Bridge at Unyeada Community and the construction of internal roads in Asarama Community embarked upon by his administration to further boost economic development in the communities. He explained that the Usabamu/Father bridge was being rehabilitated to allow for easy passage of motorists while the construction of the Asarama Internal road is intended to ease movement within the area and reduce the sufferings of the people. -Advertisement- Awortu said infrastructural development which engenders economic growth is key in the policy thrust of his administration as it has direct impact on the lives and livelihood of the people. The council Boss explained that his decision to bridge the gap on critical infrastructure in Andoni was borne out of the need to create more access roads for transportation of goods and further boost socio-economic activities in the area. He expressed satisfaction at the pace of work while tasking the Contractor on early completion ahead of expected delivery date and according to specification. The ongoing Unyeada Community Bridge and the internal road projects in Asarama Community which are over 90% completed are expected to be delivered this second quarter of the year.